The paper discusses the generation of behavior of agents that is interpretable to humans, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also discusses the concepts of security and privacy, which are relevant to computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the observer's understanding of the agent's intentions, which is related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper proposes a taxonomy of relevant concepts, which is a common theme in machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
